      <h2>A Whole-of-Home Approach to Energy</h2>
      <p>
        Most energy companies sell one product. A solar company sells panels. A plumber installs a heat pump. An electrician wires a smart switch. None of them talk to each other, and the result is a collection of products that don't work together.
      </p>
      <p>
        We take a different approach. EES designs integrated energy systems where solar, battery storage, hot water, heating and cooling, and automation all work as a single managed system. The result is lower energy bills, better comfort, and a home that runs on clean energy — not grid electricity and gas.
      </p>

      <h2>What We Install</h2>

      <h3><a href="/services/residential/solar-systems">Solar Panel Systems</a></h3>
      <p>
        Rooftop solar designed around your energy profile — not a one-size-fits-all package off a truck. We install Tier 1 panels and quality inverters, sized from 6.6 kW starter systems to 13+ kW for larger homes and EV charging. Every system is designed by a CEC-accredited installer and backed by a <strong>10-year workmanship warranty</strong>.
      </p>

      <h3><a href="/services/residential/battery-systems">Battery Storage</a></h3>
      <p>
        Store your solar energy and use it after sunset. We install home battery systems from 5 kWh to 15+ kWh, including Tesla Powerwall, Enphase, BYD, and other leading brands. Batteries reduce your grid dependence, provide backup during outages, and can be paired with off-grid or hybrid configurations. Victorian battery rebates may apply.
      </p>

      <h3><a href="/services/residential/heat-pump-systems">Heat Pump Hot Water</a></h3>
      <p>
        Our polyvalent heat pump systems produce heating, cooling, and hot water simultaneously — delivering an effective COP of up to 7:1. That means for every 1 kW of electricity in, you get up to 7 kW of useful energy out. Powered by your solar, the running cost is close to zero. No gas connection required.
      </p>

      <h3><a href="/services/residential/comfort-conditioning">Hydronic Heating & Cooling</a></h3>
      <p>
        Radiant hydronic ceiling panels heat and cool your home using circulated water — no fans, no dust, no noise. Paired with our heat pump, the entire system runs on solar electricity. Hydronic radiant heating is more comfortable and more efficient than ducted air or split systems, with even temperature distribution across every room.
      </p>

      <h3><a href="/services/residential/home-automation">Home Automation & Energy Management</a></h3>
      <p>
        A home energy management system (HEMS) ties everything together — solar monitoring, battery scheduling, heat pump control, load shifting, and smart export management. You get real-time visibility of your energy production and consumption, and the system optimises automatically so you use the least amount of grid power possible.
      </p>

      <h3><a href="/services/residential/virtual-power-plants">Virtual Power Plants (VPPs)</a></h3>
      <p>
        Turn your battery into a revenue stream. A Virtual Power Plant connects your home battery to a coordinated network — when the grid needs extra power during peak demand, your battery discharges stored energy and you get paid. We install VPP-ready battery systems and handle enrolment so you can start earning from day one.
      </p>

